    "body": "This uses the same triton kernel as flashinfer.py to prevent a CPU sync when preparing the page_indices buffer.\n\nNOTE: This is my first time working on this type of code, and I'd appreciate thorough reviews.\n\n## Purpose\nFix a long sync when running _build_decode. This was found during profiling.\n\nBefore the change:\n<img width=\"1165\" height=\"217\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/38b87662-3d1d-4d46-8984-a3a447d1dbde\" />\n\nAfter the change:\n<img width=\"1048\" height=\"203\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/5fb5fc7c-97d6-49f9-8491-e24975576f18\" />\n\n(not up to scale)\n\n## Test Plan\n- Ran DeepSeek R1 inference pre and post change\n- Captured inference output and profile\n\n## Test Result\n- Profile improved (see above), sync is gone\n- Inference output still makes sense and looks coherent\n\n---\n<details>\n<summary> Essential Elements of an Effective PR Description Checklist </summary>\n\n- [ ] The purpose of the PR, such as \"Fix some issue (link existing issues this PR will resolve)\".\n- [ ] The test plan, such as providing test command.\n- [ ] The test results, such as pasting the results comparison before and after, or e2e results\n- [ ] (Optional) The necessary documentation update, such as updating `supported_models.md` and `examples` for a new model.\n- [ ] (Optional) Release notes update. If your change is user facing, please update the release notes draft in the [Google Doc](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1YyVqrgX4gHTtrstbq8oWUImOyPCKSGnJ7xtTpmXzlRs/edit?tab=t.0).\n</details>\n\n",
